.TH "blk_queue_zone_write_granularity" 9 "blk_queue_zone_write_granularity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_queue_zone_write_granularity \- set zone write granularity for the queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" blk_queue_zone_write_granularity
.BI "(struct request_queue *q "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "q" 12
the request queue for the zoned device
.IP "size" 12
the zone write granularity size, in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should be set to the lowest possible size allowing to write in
sequential zones of a zoned block device.
